Thomas Tuchel hailed Chelsea’s professionalism in settling their FA Cup third-round clash with Chesterfield before half-time. The Blues cruised past their National League opponents 5-1 at Stamford Bridge, racing into a 4-0 half-time lead before a raft of withdrawals to keep players fresh. Debutant Lewis Hall laid on a goal for Romelu Lukaku, with the returning Belgium striker missing a trio of chances before being subbed at the break. Everton’s Reaction Pleases Benitez In Hard-Fought FA Cup Victory… Chelsea Goalkeeper Mendy Positive For Virus At African Cup Timo Werner, Callum Hudson-Odoi and Andreas Christensen all netted, before Hakim Ziyech converted a penalty. Chelsea will now move to Wednesday’s Carabao Cup semi-final second leg at Tottenham, with Tuchel delighted to press on unscathed.